<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7929548>
    dc:description "FIGURE 30. Alloglyptus crenshawi Byrd, 1950, ventral view, redrawn from Byrd (1950, figs. 1 & 2). Abbreviations: Ce, cecum; CP, cirrus-pouch; EA, excretory arm; EP, excretory pore; Es, esophagus; EV, excretory vesicle; GP, genital pore; HD, hermaphroditic duct; LT, left testis; Me, metraterm; MG, Mehlis’ gland; OS, oral sucker; Ov, ovary; Ph, pharynx; PP, pars prostatica; RT, right testis; SR, seminal receptacle; SV, seminal vesicle; Ut, uterus; VD, vitelline duct; VF, vitelline follicle; VR, vitelline reservoir; VS, ventral sucker. Scale bar: Fig. 30 = 1,000 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7929548/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

